Kelly Watson, 41, from Gateshead, Tyne and Wear, started having problems three years ago when she began struggling with words and co-ordination .
She was diagnosed with early-onset dementia on her 41st birthday on June 23 last year .
The mother-of-one is now terrified of forgetting her 17-year-old daughter, Holly .
Kelly now attends a dementia support group five days a week and is the youngest by 20 years .